{"nodes": [{"id": "draft6_0_src_stage2_report", "label": "Stage 2 Report (P7-9, the namer)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\stage2-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": null}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_phase9_final_architecture", "label": "phase9-final-architecture v2.0.0 (whole two-brain model)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\stage2-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The self-contained account of the complete frozen two-brain neocortex \u2014 the object Phase 10/11 race."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_stage2_report_slda_namer", "label": "SLDA namer (the deployed closed-form head)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\stage2-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Streaming, closed-form, no gradient, no backward pass; a tied-covariance discriminant. Committed as the DEPLOYED head at P8 (metered 69x cheaper than RanPAC, ties its live accuracy). The '20% GD' is a role, not a method."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_stage2_report_ranpac_namer", "label": "RanPAC namer (frozen random projection + ridge prototype)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\stage2-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Random ReLU projection -> running-Gram ridge prototype W=(G+lambdaI)^-1 M, no gradient, streaming. P7 bake-off winner + cbrs guard; kept as accuracy/spine reference after P8's meter takes SLDA as the ~200x cheaper fallback."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_stage2_report_ddm_gate", "label": "DDM awake gate (on the namer's error-EMA)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\stage2-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "S6/S12 \u2014 the two-threshold drift detector that fires the namer only when the cheap path stalls; consumes an error rate. The gate is a SAFETY mechanism: firing more forgets more (always-pay -0.137)."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_stage2_report_tap_drift_trigger", "label": "Class-direction tap-drift trigger (validated, not shipped)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\stage2-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "P8.2 \u2014 a label-free SCFF-tap direction watcher: leads the labeled error by ~8 steps, nuisance-invariant, while the magnitude-of-shift null false-fires on 94% of nuisance steps. Not deployed (DDM consumes an error rate) -> the north-star gate seed."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_stage2_report_cbrs_eviction", "label": "CBRS eviction (class-balanced reservoir sampling)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\stage2-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "P7.3/P9.3 \u2014 buffer-side class balancing beats output re-weighting (AIR over-corrects). Best-bounded eviction policy: keeps prototypes balanced so it spans class directions at a tight budget; cap grows with class count."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_stage2_report_proto_reanchor", "label": "Proto-reanchor (read-side noise defense)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\stage2-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "P9.4 \u2014 re-forward the raw LUT through the current bulk under the SAME device offset, producing drift-free, shift-consistent prototypes. Recovers the Phase-6 input-transducer directional residual 0.79->0.99. The sleep mechanism applied under shift; no new organ."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_stage2_report_frozen_object", "label": "The frozen object (commit 59d2720)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\stage2-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "S13 \u2014 the complete two-brain neocortex locked at P9: NoiseAugContrast bulk + SLDA namer + DDM/error-EMA gate + CBRS + all-tap sleep + proto-reanchor + grid-4 cadence. Touched no knob after; freeze_content guard asserts bit-for-bit reproduction."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_stage2_report_metered_8020", "label": "Metered 80/20 economy (the gate as safety)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\stage2-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "P8.5/P8.7 \u2014 first hardware number for the founding split: GD-share 0.121 with the gate on (0.778 off; the gate CREATES it). The chip is 15.4x cheaper than GD-on-digital = 5.4x substrate (CIM) x 2.9x algorithm."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_stage2_report_freeze_judge_discipline", "label": "Freeze in P9, judge in P10 (the discipline)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\stage2-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The honesty cut: the object was locked before any baseline number existed; verdict shapes pinned BLIND before the racer ran. Never tune against the baseline you are judged by."}], "edges": [{"source": "draft6_0_src_stage2_report", "target": "draft6_0_src_stage1_report", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\stage2-report.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_src_stage2_report", "target": "draft6_0_src_validation_report", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\stage2-report.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0